Your Honor,

I, David Lambert, plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I stand before you today to take responsibility for my actions and to express my deepest remorse for the violation I have committed.

I must admit that my actions were indeed a result of a momentary lapse in judgement. I acknowledge that I should have been aware of the court's previous order, which disqualified me from driving. However, in my thoughtlessness, I failed to consider the consequences of my actions and drove to the supermarket. I understand the severity of my offense and the importance of abiding by the court's orders.

While I deeply regret my behavior, I would like to assure the court that this incident is an anomaly in an otherwise clean record. I have never been involved in any criminal activity before, and the disqualification from driving was the first encounter I had with the legal system. This demonstrates that I am a law-abiding citizen who made an unfortunate mistake.

Your Honor, I would like to address the court's attention to my age. At 55 years old, I have reached a stage in life where I am expected to show wisdom and responsibility. Regrettably, I failed to meet these expectations in this instance. Nevertheless, my age does not excuse my behavior, but it does indicate that I am capable of learning from my mistakes and ensuring that such incidents do not repeat in the future.

I understand the significance and impact of my actions, not only on myself but also on society. I am committed to making amends for my behavior and taking the necessary steps to prevent a similar offense from occurring again. I am willing to undergo a driving safety course or any other educational program that the court deems necessary to ensure I fully comprehend the gravity of my actions and become a more responsible member of society.

Furthermore, I would like to emphasize that I am truly sorry for any inconvenience or harm I may have caused. Although there was no physical harm in this case, I acknowledge that my actions were a disregard for the law and for the safety of others on the road. I assure the court that I have reflected on my behavior and the potential consequences it could have had.

Your Honor, it is my sincere hope that you take into consideration my guilty plea as a significant mitigating factor. I humbly ask for your mercy and leniency in sentencing, taking into account my previous good character and my willingness to make amends.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court today.

