I, David Lambert, plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I stand before you today to take responsibility for my actions and express my deepest remorse for the violation I have committed.

I must acknowledge that my actions were indeed a result of a momentary lapse in judgment. Despite being disqualified from driving due to four speeding incidents two months ago, I regrettably failed to consider the consequences of my actions. I made the ill-advised decision to get in the car and drive to a supermarket while fully aware of my disqualification.

I understand the gravity of my offense and the importance of abiding by the court's orders. The fact that I drove to a supermarket while disqualified is something I deeply regret. It was irresponsible and a clear violation of the court's previous order.

At 55 years old, I am expected to display wisdom and responsibility. I fully recognize that I should have acted more responsibly and made better decisions. The fact that this incident occurred is deeply embarrassing and out of character for me. However, I believe it is important to emphasize that this is an exception rather than a reflection of who I am as an individual.

Your Honor, I assure you that I am dedicated to learning from this mistake and ensuring personal growth. I am committed to becoming a law-abiding citizen once again. I understand the importance of rehabilitation and accountability and am ready to take the necessary steps to make positive changes in my life.

I deeply regret any harm I may have caused by my actions and the inconvenience it may have caused others. I humbly ask for your mercy and leniency in sentencing, considering my guilty plea and my determination to become a responsible member of society once again.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court today.

